author: cmlenz
msg: When creating a revision descriptor at bootstrap, that descriptor might
already exist. The current behaviour is to pretty much ignore that fact,
and effectively just update the old descriptor.
With the new schema and all it's integrity constraints that led to
exceptions, because we were trying to insert duplicate revision
properties. As a (lame) workaround, all properties (and labels)
associated with the revision to be created are first deleted.
